  "poem": {
    "content": "The orchard sleeps, heavy with denial,\na narrow path where shadows play.\n\nI shrug, a transfer of unease,\nwatching ducks, gray smudges in the bay.\n\nHe marches on, a medal bright as scorn,\nwhile fluid dreams slip through my hold.\n\nA silly trick, this longing in the air,\nleaving stories yet untold.\n\nAerobic breaths, to chase the sullen frown,\nmuch laughter lost beneath the trees.\n\nA stolen pizza, shared in fading light,\na flimsy promise on the breeze.\n\nMy blush, a subtle stain upon the skin,\nbetrays the hope I cannot tame.\n\nThis fragile heart against the coming dark,\nwhispering secrets, naming names.\n\nAnd even as the branches claw and reach,\na new resolve begins to grow.",
